---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Australia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/australia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'New Zealand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/new-zealand' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'australiaFit', header: 'Australia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'A$520-720/mo', australiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'A$580-800/mo', australiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'A$450-620/mo', australiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'A$420-580/mo', australiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Australian Private Health', entryAge: '65+', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'A$300-600/mo', australiaFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'A$450-720', annual: 'A$5,400-8,640' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'A$620-900', annual: 'A$7,440-10,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'A$820-1,200', annual: 'A$9,840-14,400' },
  { category: 'Australian Private Health (Senior)', monthly: 'A$300-600', annual: 'A$3,600-7,200' },
  { category: 'Medicare (PR/Citizens)', monthly: 'Free base', annual: 'Tax-funded' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Australia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Australia. Medicare access, private health options, visa requirements, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Australia"
  subheadline="Australia offers excellent healthcare, outdoor lifestyle, and English-speaking culture—but strict immigration requires family ties or significant assets."
  heroImage="/images/countries/australia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Australia</h2>
  <p>
    Australia combines first-world healthcare, stunning natural beauty, and an outdoor lifestyle with the comfort of English language and Western culture. For seniors from the UK, Ireland, or other Commonwealth countries, the cultural transition is relatively smooth.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sydney and Melbourne offer world-class medical facilities and cultural amenities. Brisbane and the Gold Coast provide warmer climates. Perth offers Mediterranean-like weather. Adelaide and Tasmania appeal to those seeking slower-paced living with excellent healthcare access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; ranked top 15 globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> A$3,500-5,500/month depending on city</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varies; tropical north, temperate south, Mediterranean west</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Very safe; low crime rates</li>
      <li><strong>Immigration:</strong> Strict; age limits on most visas</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Australia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Medicare provides free or subsidized healthcare to Australian citizens and permanent residents. Public hospitals provide free treatment, while private hospitals offer choice of doctor, shorter waits, and private rooms (covered by private health insurance).
  </p>

  <p>
    The Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme (PBS) heavily subsidizes prescription medications. GP visits are often bulk-billed (free) or low cost. Specialist care may have gaps between Medicare rebate and doctor's fee.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Immigration Challenge</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Australia has strict immigration policies, especially for older applicants. Most skilled visas have age limits of 45-50. The Parent visa has significant costs (A$50,000+) and long wait times (30+ years for non-contributory). Plan carefully if considering Australia as a retirement destination.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Australia's immigration system is challenging for retirees without family connections:
  </p>

  <h3>Contributory Parent Visa (Subclass 143)</h3>
  <p>
    If you have children who are Australian citizens/PRs. Costs A$50,000+ per person, but processing is faster (2-4 years). Grants Medicare access once PR granted.
  </p>

  <h3>Non-Contributory Parent Visa (Subclass 103)</h3>
  <p>
    Lower cost (~A$7,000) but wait times are 30+ years. Not practical for most seniors.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Retirement Visa (Subclass 405) - Closed</h3>
  <p>
    This visa is no longer available for new applicants. Existing holders may renew.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Visa (Subclass 600)</h3>
  <p>
    Grants 3-12 months stay. Can be extended to 12 months maximum. No Medicare access—comprehensive travel insurance required.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs depend entirely on your visa status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Citizens/PRs:</strong> Medicare access; may add private health for faster care</li>
    <li><strong>Parent visa holders:</strong> Medicare once PR granted; private during processing</li>
    <li><strong>Visitors:</strong> No Medicare; must have comprehensive travel/health insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Reciprocal countries:</strong> UK, NZ, Ireland citizens have some Medicare access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Lifetime Health Cover Loading</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Australia penalizes late purchase of private health insurance. If you're over 31 when you first buy PHI, you pay a 2% loading per year over 30, up to 70%. This makes early PHI purchase important for those planning to stay long-term.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Australia, both international and local providers offer options:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Australia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Australian network, direct billing at major hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), BUPA also operates in Australia locally</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good value, solid Australian coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Australian PHI:</strong> For PR holders, local private health provides hospital cover and extras</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Australia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Australia has high healthcare costs, reflected in insurance premiums:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Medicare primary:</strong> If you have Medicare, use it as primary coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> A$500-1,000 excess reduces PHI premiums significantly</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital-only:</strong> Skip extras cover (dental, optical) if budget-constrained</li>
    <li><strong>Reciprocal agreements:</strong> UK citizens get some Medicare access; leverage this</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Parent Visa Applicant, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Son is Australian citizen. Applying for Contributory Parent Visa (143). Processing time ~3 years.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global during processing. Reciprocal Medicare access for UK citizens covers emergencies.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~A$700/month during processing. Once PR granted, switch to Medicare + local PHI.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Long-Stay Visitor, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 12-month visitor visa to spend time near grandchildren. No pathway to PR.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global comprehensive coverage. No Medicare access; need full international coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~A$850/month. Essential for hospital care at A$1,000-2,000/night private rates.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: New PR Holder, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Just received PR through family. Enrolling in Medicare. Considering private health.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Medicare for base coverage. Add local PHI for hospital (shorter waits) and international for travel.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Medicare (free) + PHI A$400/month + travel policy for overseas visits.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Australia without family there?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult. Australia doesn't have a standalone retirement visa. The investor visa (405) is closed. Without Australian citizen/PR children or significant business investment, long-term residence is challenging. Some retirees use repeated visitor visas, but this doesn't provide Medicare or stability.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Australia's healthcare compare globally?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent quality, ranked in top 15 globally. Medicare provides comprehensive coverage for residents. Specialist care is world-class. Wait times for elective surgery in public system can be months; private health speeds this up.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about reciprocal healthcare agreements?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Australia has Medicare reciprocal agreements with UK, Ireland, New Zealand, Sweden, Netherlands, Finland, Norway, Belgium, Slovenia, Malta, and Italy. These provide emergency and essential care for visitors, but NOT comprehensive coverage. Still need travel insurance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Australian private health insurance expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Relatively expensive for seniors due to community rating (everyone pays similar) plus lifetime loading (2% per year over 30). Expect A$300-600/month for comprehensive hospital + extras cover for someone 65+.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Australia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Australian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
